The judgment is not yet enforceable; in December the appeal of the defendants to the Court of Justice is to be negotiated.
Timoshenko himself refers to the judgment as political revenge of the regime and also in the West the trial raised the suspicion of preconception of the court.
The request to remove paragraph 365, on the basis of which the Prime Minister was condemned to be removed from the Criminal Code, was supported by 147 MEPs.
226 votes would have been necessary for its adoption.
