The appointed Prime Minister, Mario Monti, will meet with the President of Italy tomorrow to introduce the new government that is expected to present the crisis that has led Italy to the brink of economic collapse.
A communication from the Presidency Palace announced that the Monti, appointed on Sunday, would meet with the President, Giorgio Napolitano, on Wednesday to confirm the formation of the government.
