Monti said he would present to the President the results of talks with the political parties on government formation.
"I want to reaffirm my absolute confidence in our country's ability to cope with these difficult times," said the former EU Commissioner to the journalists.
Monti did not explicitly confirm government formation, but his comments show that the obstacles have been overcome.
"The frame is now well positioned," he added.
Monti has managed to create a government in less than three days, which is much less time than normal. Meanwhile, Italy is fighting a political and financial crisis that has driven the cost of debt to an unbearable level.
The new government, led by former EU Commissioner Monti, must adopt a tough austerity package called for by the euro-politicians to regain confidence in Italy.
