The former president Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital on Tuesday to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is 25 years in prison for human rights violations during his reign (1990-2000), has several diseases, including tongue cancer, which is operated four times and controlled.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Congressman and his personal doctor, told television that Fujimori would be examined for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to determine the cause of his pain and muscle loss in the lower body members.
Aguinaga commented that, in his opinion, Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons. Nevertheless, he did not wish to do so because he considered him innocent.
He was operated four times on cancer of the tongue and he has lost 18 kilos of weight. In addition to other diseases such as severe erosion of gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and blood circulation problems in the legs, the doctor counted up.
Fujimori has been in the Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía Detention Centre since September 2007.
