Occupyed house where giant parties were held was cleared
The owners had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on Balmes No. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve occupants left the building yesterday afternoon without having done any resistance.
Everything points out that the nightmares of the neighbors of the house No. 51 on Balmes Street have ended.
Twelve people voluntarily left yesterday afternoon the building that they had been illegally occupied and in which they had organized huge festivals that had driven the neighborhood to despair. The evacuation took place on judicial order without police intervention.
After the evacuation, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, access will be controlled," confirmed the house manager.
The housekeepers, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the others were inhabited - took along the entire electrical system and part of the water supply. Moreover, they had painted the walls and left all kinds of garbage, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
On the three lower floors, huge parties were celebrated, lasting up to two days and driving the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also suffered damage from it.
Her owner, Maria Pantinat, told Europe Press that her business had decreased by 80% since the start of the house occupation.
The owner of the discotheque pointed out that the homeowners made their unfair competition, because they sold the drinks to three euros, while they cost 10 euros in the discotheque.
