The head of the discotheque explained that the harassment had been so great that she agreed with the owner of the building that she did not have to pay rent for the last nine months.
The Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that she had received more complaints from neighbors in recent weeks.
The president of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in Barcelona City Council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, last week asked to clear the building immediately and get the problems of bourgeois cohabitation and the downfall of the district.
