So was the work of the doctor who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Lophoscopist from Cali entered history as the man who identified "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials plays a key role.
Last November 4th, a lophoscopy of the unit of investigation of the Cali Procuratorate (CTI) confirmed the identity of the leader of the FARC (Fuerzas Armadas Revolucionarias de Colombia - Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia): "Alfonso Cano" by comparison of fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists in the CTI department, this week Eliazar González had been on standby, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been involved in criminal investigations for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in communities of Chocó, where he often had to go to the jungle for five days to reach the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000 he settled after Valle over and after completing the required courses he specialized in lophoscopy, which is the examination of the skin that is exposed to friction, i.e. the hand and foot surfaces.
In the week of the operation against the so-called Alfonso Cano, Eliasar was advised to pack clothes for at least three days.
Something big awaited him.
He flew from Palmira to Cauca in the helicopter on Friday night.
He knew that he should identify two bodies, and that the suspicion was that one of the man who had led the oldest guerrilla in the world could be. Therefore, he should take along the ten-finger print sheet of Guillermo León Sáenz (his actual name).
However, when he reached the place where the body was located with the investigator, he could not identify it because of his physical appearance, because this was not the least like the pictures he had seen in the mass media.
He had no beard, was dressed like a farmer in the area, wore no glasses and was much thinner.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Armed with a magnifying glass, ink, a plant cellar and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body to those on the printing sheet.
He had seen it right: it was "Alfonso Cano".
The same night, this man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for telling Juan Carlos Pinzón that it was actually the head of the FARC.
On Track Search
The appreciation given by President Juan Manuel Santos Eliasar González at a press conference on the use of "cano" was very important for a daktyloskope from Sijín in Cali.
Many people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science with no error rate, which can be a key factor in resolving a crime.
Lophoscopeists not only identify bodies, they also support investigations into murder and robbery and confirm the identity of the arrested persons.
When they are arrested, many offenders present false identity documents or they have none.
We'll take them off the fingerprints and find them in the database.
The researcher told us that he had to tear a piece of wall out of a house with a theft, because the thief had supported himself with his hand at this very place, when he pulled out a box full of jewelry and money.
"walls are difficult because their surfaces are unsuitable for fingerprinting. But in this case we could take the print of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in several thefts," he remembered.
With the help of fingerprints, murder suspects can also be relieved or burdened.
Recently, a dead man was found surrounded by bottles of schnapp.
In the investigation, it was suspected that a family member might be suspect, and in fact, a fingerprint on the bottle agreed.
Although this does not guarantee that it is the murderer, it is linked to the place where the crime was committed.
A CTI dactyloscopy stated that "the fingerprints were taken from the object with chemical or physical reagents."
If they appear, a plant cell or a tape is used to take them.
After that, the prints are sent to the Asif, that's the crime database, or to the stand office.
"The problem is that there are still many Colombians without ID cards," said the CTI expert.
He said not everything was the same as it was shown in the TV series SCI.
Just as not all gold shines, not everything you touch is a fingerprint.
But it can still be used if you make a corresponding comparison.
